<center>
<h1>CASE Computer-Aided Software Engineering</h1>
</center>

<font color="red">
<b>Upper-CASE</b> are front-end tools, such as tools for requirements,
specification, planning and design.

<p>
<b>Lower-CASE</b> are back-end tools, such as tools for implementation,
code generation, integration and maintenance.
<p>
<b>Data dictionary</b> can be used for storing information about
data items.

<p>
<b>Consistency Checker</b> checks every data item in the spec is
reflected in the design, and then the code, etc. and vice versa.

<p>
<b>Report Generator</b> generates codes for reports.

<p>
<b>Screen Generator</b> generates codes for screens.

<p>
<b>Workbench</b> supports rapid prototyping by combining the above.

<p>
<b>Environment</b> supports the complete software process
(sometimes called <b>SEE</b> or Software Engineering Environment).

